This paper explores the impact of humanoid robot expressive language on human behavior and perception in a competitive game, which falls under the intersection of robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also contributes a Natural Language Processing framework, which could be relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG).
